S'"Accupedo Pedometer Widget made good walking buddies in our last tests." [Washington Post, 10/1/12] "Among cellphone apps the Accupedo pedometer widget for Android phones had the top spot." [LA Times, 12/28/11]Accupedo is an accurate Pedometer Widget that monitors your daily walking on the Home screen.  ++++ ATTENTION ++++ Your phone may not compatible with Accupedo. Some phones do not support the G-sensor in SLEEP (STANDBY, when screen is OFF) mode by those phone manufacturers. This is not a defect of this app. Accupedo is a free edition of Accupedo-Pro. Chart will be disabled after 7 day trial period.An intelligent 3D motion recognition algorithm is embedded to track only walking patterns by filtering and ejecting out non walking activities. Accupedo counts your steps regardless of where you put your phone like your pocket, waist belt, or bag. Be healthy by setting up your daily goal and accurately monitoring your steps with Accupedo. ++++ Features  ++++\xe2\x97\x8f The intelligent algorithm starts tracking after 4 - 12 CONSECUTIVE steps, then stops and restarts automatically as you walk.\xe2\x97\x8f Customizable widget display modes: steps, distance, minutes, calories, and Trip A.\xe2\x97\x8f Daily log history: step counts, distance, calories, and walking time.\xe2\x97\x8f Customized power usage mode options for efficient power saving.\xe2\x97\x8f Daily active hour option for power saving.\xe2\x97\x8f Customized personal settings: sensitivity, metric/english, step distance, body weight, daily goal, etc.\xe2\x97\x8f Concise widget display on Home screen.\xe2\x97\x8f A \xe2\x80\x9codometer\xe2\x80\x9d function for steps (Trip A)\xe2\x97\x8f Resume/Pause/Reset\xe2\x97\x8f Widget skin colors: black, blue, green, orange, pink\xe2\x97\x8f Screen on/off option\xe2\x97\x8f Email a daily log file\xe2\x97\x8f Manual step count addition and subtraction\xe2\x97\x8f Language option: default and English ++++ Installation  ++++\xe2\x97\x8f After downloading, press and hold your finger on the EMPTY space of the Home screen. (If your Home screen is FULL of Apps, remove at least two adjacent App because Accupedo needs two App space to install it.) \xe2\x80\x9cAdd to Home screen\xe2\x80\x9d menu will appear with options listing.\xe2\x97\x8f Select Widgets from the menu, and then select the widget named \xe2\x80\x9cAccupedo\xe2\x80\x9d.\xe2\x97\x8f Try moving it around by pressing and holding your finger on the widget.\xe2\x97\x8f WATCH YOUTUBE FOR INSTALLATION VIDEO (Type in Accupedo)  for more information.  ++++  Notes  ++++ \xe2\x97\x8f It works only for an Android phone with G-sensor (accelerometer).\xe2\x97\x8f It performs best when the phone is on your waist belt.\xe2\x97\x8f Step count may not be accurate if you put your phone in loose fit pants due to the random movement your phone makes in the pocket.\xe2\x97\x8f The sensitivity of a phone can be different from others. So, choose a sensitivity level that works best for your phone.\xe2\x97\x8f Help and FAQ are built in the App.Recent changes:Version 3.1.5 (April 12, 2013)-----------------------------------\xe2\x97\x8f Fixed an error for small screen phonesVersion 3.1.3 (April 12, 2013)-----------------------------------\xe2\x97\x8f Optimized program.\xe2\x97\x8f Exit menu is added.*** Widget cannot be opened at SD-Card. Save Accupedo to phone memory.'
